      "content": "Visually, you would see the myofibrils, the muscle's contractile units, experiencing stretch and microscopic separation when under heavy load. Following the strain, satellite cells—which look like small, rounded nuclei outside the main muscle fiber—would become activated, migrating towards the damaged areas. You'd observe them fusing their membranes with the existing fiber, donating their nuclei to promote the muscle's subsequent growth and repair.",
